   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sustainable integration of internally displaced populations (IDPs) in north-east Nigeria (Shelter/Non-Food Items (NFI</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving shelter and essential household item assistance to internally displaced people in Northeast Nigeria. This IOM project constructs 300 transitional mudbrick shelters with latrine and shower facilities, and distributes essential household item kits. The project provides life-saving assistance to 1,500 people, including 370 women, 290 men, 840 children, and 80 persons with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
